At Hough Ear Institute the bench model 's functional gain ( FG ) in dB SPL is defined as :

( 2-1 ) FG = dB SP L out - dB SPL in ( 2-1 )

or

( 2-2 ) FG = 20 log ( P out /P ref ) - 20 log ( P in /P ref )

where P ref = 20 microPascals ( Mu Pa ) , the standard reference sound pressure used in audiological measurement ; P out is the output sound pressure calculated from peak-to-peak displacements of the implant in bench testing system ; and P in is the calibrated input sound pressure from audiometer .

d. creation of a facility separate from the production data to isolate programs being tested
